July 10, 2026 (continued — per-module assertions classes)

- Created BookingsAssertions, AdminAssertions, WorkersAssertions as @Injectable() classes
  in [name].assertions.ts; each holds all module-specific assertion methods (validate + throw)
- Updated bookings.module.ts, admin.module.ts, workers.module.ts to register assertions
  classes in providers
- Refactored bookings.service.ts, admin.service.ts, workers.service.ts: inject assertions
  class via constructor; replace this.assertX() with this.assertions.assertX(); remove
  private assertion methods and Private: assertions divider (now only two dividers per service)
- Updated all spec files to mock assertions class entirely, eliminating deep prisma mock
  chains for assertion-path tests; fixed bookings.controller.spec.ts to also provide
  BookingsAssertions mock
- Updated CLAUDE.md module conventions and .claude/commands/implement.md with assertions
  class pattern and two-divider service structure rule

