July 10, 2026 (continued — code review fixes)

- Added assertUserIsActive to UsersAssertions; swapped assertUserExists -> assertUserIsActive
  at all call sites where suspended users must be blocked (bookings create/cancel/prepareBookingAction,
  workers createProfile); assertUserExists kept for admin lookups that need suspended users
- Guarded cancel() against non-CUSTOMER/WORKER callers: previously both role branches were
  silently skipped for any other role, letting bookings be unconditionally cancelled
- Fixed customers.service.createProfile 404 bug: replaced this.getProfile() (which throws
  NotFoundException when no profile exists) with a direct findUnique so first-time creation works
- Added isOnline: false to workerProfile suspension in handleWorkerCancellationPenalty, matching
  admin.incrementStrikeAndSuspendIfNeeded; suspended workers now correctly go offline

